Key Match Events: Reid Detmers struck out 10 batters over six innings in his return to the Majors.
Shohei Ohtani hit an RBI triple and scored on an RBI single from Mookie Betts.
Mookie Betts hit a three-run homer in the 10th inning after an intentional walk to Shohei Ohtani.
Post-Match Reflections: Reid Detmers expressed happiness about his return and performance against the Dodgers.
Manager Ron Washington praised Detmers' command and use of offspeed pitches.
Catcher Logan O’Hoppe reflected on the game, mentioning the need to knock off some rust initially but eventually getting back to normal.
Miscellaneous Highlights: Reid Detmers retired the last 11 batters he faced, including striking out Will Smith to end the sixth inning.
Detmers had a solid stretch in Triple-A with a 1.29 ERA and 29 strikeouts in 21 innings over his last three starts.
